2. Table Design
Four tables are sufficient to drive the full state machine at runtime. The three config tables (Delivery Class C) are loaded manually in the MVP. ZCASTAT_LOG (Delivery Class A) is written exclusively by ZCL_CA_STATUSMANAGER.
2.1 ZCASTAT_TYPE
Field
Type
Key
Notes
status_type_id
CHAR(40)
PK
Start with Z or Y
status_type_description
CHAR(100)


Display label
business_object_type
CHAR(30)


DDIC table or CDS entity name (informational in MVP)
is_active
XFELD


Must be X for runtime use
created_by_user / created_at
SYUNAME / UTCLONG


Audit fields — stamped manually in MVP
changed_by_user / changed_at
SYUNAME / UTCLONG


ETag in Phase 2 RAP BO


ZCASTAT_CODE has the same key pattern (STATUS_TYPE_ID + STATUS_CODE) plus STATUS_LABEL, CRITICALITY (INT1), IS_INITIAL, IS_FINAL, IS_ACTIVE, and audit fields. ZCASTAT_ACTION key is STATUS_TYPE_ID + FROM_STATUS_CODE + TO_STATUS_CODE + ACTION_CODE, plus ACTION_NAME, REQUIRES_COMMENT, AUTHORIZATION_OBJECT, IS_ACTIVE, and audit fields. See the full design document (v11) for complete field definitions.
2.2 ZCASTAT_LOG (append-only)
Field
Type
Notes
log_uuid
SYSUUID_16
PK — collision-free, no serialization needed
log_sequence
INT8
Human-readable reference + sort key. Best-effort from ZCASTAT_NR. Value 0 if unavailable.
status_type_id
CHAR(40)
FK → ZCASTAT_TYPE
business_obj_key
CHAR(90)
Concatenated key of the business object instance
from_status_code / to_status_code
CHAR(20)
from_status_code empty on initial CREATE transition
action_code / remark
CHAR(20) / CHAR(255)
Action that triggered the transition + optional user remark
changed_at / changed_date / changed_time
UTCLONG / DATS / TIMS
Three-field timestamp strategy: UTC precision + SE16N-readable local date/time


3. Manager Class API
ZCL_CA_STATUSMANAGER is the only write path to ZCASTAT_LOG. All five public methods are stateless — instantiate once per call or hold one instance per request context.
Method
Description
change_status
Acquires enqueue lock, resolves current and target status, validates config, calls BAdI VALIDATE_TRANSITION, writes log entry, calls BAdI AFTER_TRANSITION, releases lock. iv_from_status_code and iv_to_status_code are both optional — auto-resolved when unambiguous. Raises ZCX_CA_STATUS_ERROR on any failure.
get_current_status
Returns the to_status_code of the most recent log entry for a business object instance. Uses ORDER BY log_sequence DESC, changed_at DESC. Returns initial value if no log entries exist.
get_log
Returns all ZCASTAT_LOG entries for a business object instance, ordered chronologically ascending by log_sequence, changed_at. Used by the consuming app to render a status timeline.
get_available_actions
Returns all active ZCASTAT_ACTION rows for a given from_status_code and status_type_id. Use this to build action buttons in the consuming app UI without coupling to the table name.
is_transition_allowed
Dry-run validation without acquiring the lock or writing any entry. Returns ABAP_TRUE if the action is currently valid. Use for UI enablement checks (button visible/enabled logic).


3.1 change_status internal sequence
#
Step
Key detail
①
ENQUEUE_EZCASTAT_LOCK
Mode E, _scope=2, _wait=false. Raises CONCURRENT_LOCK on foreign_lock.
②
Resolve current status
Safe after lock. Auto from log if iv_from_status_code not supplied.
③
Resolve target status
Auto when exactly one active action matches. Raises AMBIGUOUS_ACTION if two or more qualify.
④
Validate configuration
Active row must exist in ZCASTAT_ACTION for from+to+type. Raises INVALID_TRANSITION.
⑤
BAdI VALIDATE_TRANSITION
Blocking. Filter on status_type_id. No-op if no implementation active.
⑥
Write log entry
SYSUUID_16 PK + best-effort log_sequence from ZCASTAT_NR + three-field timestamp.
⑦
BAdI AFTER_TRANSITION
Non-blocking. Exceptions caught and logged. Transition already committed. Receives iv_log_uuid.
⑧
DEQUEUE_EZCASTAT_LOCK
Explicit release. Also auto-released on COMMIT/ROLLBACK via _scope=2.


4. Activation Sequence
Step
Action
Detail
1
abapgit pull
Pull ZStatusFramework_MVP_abapgit.zip into development system
2
Domains + data elements (SE11)
Activate all 7 via mass activation
3
Tables (SE11)
Activate: ZCASTAT_TYPE → ZCASTAT_CODE → ZCASTAT_ACTION → ZCASTAT_LOG. Verify delivery class C/A.
4
Lock object (SE11)
Create EZCASTAT_LOCK. Table: ZCASTAT_LOG. Mode E. Fields: STATUS_TYPE_ID + BUSINESS_OBJ_KEY.
5
Number range (SNRO)
Create ZCASTAT_NR. Interval 01, 0000000001–9999999999. Buffered, size 10.
6
BAdI (SE19)
Create ESPOT_ZCASTAT + BADI_ZCASTAT_TRANSITION. Filter STATUS_TYPE_ID typed with ZCASTAT_E_TYPEID (CHAR 40). Multiple-use: Yes.
7
Message class (SE91)
Create ZCASTAT_MSG with 6 exception texts (see README).
8
ABAP objects (ADT / SE24)
Activate in order: ZCX_CA_STATUS_ERROR → ZIFI_CA_STAT_TRANSITION → ZCL_CA_STATUSMANAGER
9
Seed data (SE16N)
Insert one row in ZCASTAT_TYPE, status codes in ZCASTAT_CODE, transitions in ZCASTAT_ACTION.


5. Usage Example
DATA lo_mgr TYPE REF TO zcl_ca_statusmanager.
lo_mgr = NEW #( ).

" --- Execute a transition ---
TRY.
  lo_mgr->change_status(
    iv_status_type_id   = 'ZMM_PO_REQUEST'
    iv_business_obj_key = ls_po-ebeln
    iv_action_code      = 'APPROVE'
    iv_remark           = 'Verified and approved' ).
  COMMIT WORK AND WAIT.
CATCH zcx_ca_status_error INTO DATA(lx).
  ROLLBACK WORK.
  MESSAGE lx->get_text( ) TYPE 'E'.
ENDTRY.

" --- Read current status ---
DATA(lv_status) = lo_mgr->get_current_status(
  iv_status_type_id   = 'ZMM_PO_REQUEST'
  iv_business_obj_key = ls_po-ebeln ).

" --- Build action buttons for current state ---
DATA(lt_actions) = lo_mgr->get_available_actions(
  iv_status_type_id   = 'ZMM_PO_REQUEST'
  iv_from_status_code = lv_status ).

" --- Check before enabling a button ---
IF lo_mgr->is_transition_allowed(
     iv_status_type_id   = 'ZMM_PO_REQUEST'
     iv_business_obj_key = ls_po-ebeln
     iv_action_code      = 'APPROVE' ) = abap_true.
  " enable Approve button
ENDIF.
6. Phase 2 Path
Pull the full ZStatusFramework_abapgit repository to add the visual ProcessFlow layer, the draft-enabled RAP configuration Fiori app, and the deletion guards. The four MVP tables and ZCL_CA_STATUSMANAGER are identical between MVP and the full version — no migration or data conversion is required. The full repository adds objects on top of the MVP without modifying any existing object.
